author: COMSOL
description: Sensitivity analysis is an efficient way of computing the gradient of an objective function with respect to many control variables. This example uses the pitch and yaw in the top of a truss tower as objective functions. The sensitivity of these angles with respect to changes in the diameters of the individual bars are computed.
label: tower_sensitivity.mph
